                            <comment id="270876" author="ofaaland" created="Thu, 21 May 2020 23:05:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Jian,&lt;br/&gt;
Your b2_12 patch stack for the 4.18.0-193.el8 kernel, pushed May 2, needs to be rebased because there are conflicts with patches that landed to b2_12 since then (eb45b5 &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11089&quot; title=&quot;Performance improvements for lu_object locking&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11089&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11089&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; obd: use wait_event_var() in lu_context_key_degister() at least).  Disregard if you already knew this, and thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="270238" author="ofaaland" created="Thu, 14 May 2020 17:38:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the e2fsprogs ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="270237" author="yujian" created="Thu, 14 May 2020 17:29:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Olaf,&lt;br/&gt;
The e2fsprogs update ticket is &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13558&quot; title=&quot;upgrade e2fsprogs to 1.45.5&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13558&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13558&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. There are some failures need to be resolved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="270130" author="yujian" created="Wed, 13 May 2020 23:44:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, Olaf.&lt;br/&gt;
The full group test sessions showed that there are three new failures specific for RHEL 8.2: &lt;br/&gt;
sanity-hsm test 90 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13543&quot; title=&quot;hsm.actions file is broken on RHEL 8.2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13543&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13543&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), test 104 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13544&quot; title=&quot;sanity-hsm test_104: Data field in records is () and not ([434541])&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13544&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13544&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) and test 260c (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13545&quot; title=&quot;sanity-hsm test_260c: FAIL: request on 0x200000404:0x2bb:0x0 is not SUCCEED on mds1 &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13545&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13545&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;br/&gt;
Ben is working on them.&lt;br/&gt;
I will ask Minh about the progress of updating ldiskfsprogs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="270128" author="ofaaland" created="Wed, 13 May 2020 23:16:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;br/&gt;
Do you have any update on this (other than the new kernel RH released)?&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="270125" author="yujian" created="Wed, 13 May 2020 22:49:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New kernel version: 4.18.0-193.1.2.el8_2&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---8/x86_64/RHSA-2020:2102&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---8/x86_64/RHSA-2020:2102&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="269839" author="ofaaland" created="Mon, 11 May 2020 17:09:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Minh,&lt;br/&gt;
Do you know if that ldiskfsprogs update is a big project or a small one?  Also, is there a reason not to have an LU-ticket for it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
